AN APPARENT spike in a rare childhood illness, Kawasaki disease, suggests the coronavirus may manifest very differently in children and raises questions over the role they play in spreading the pandemic. America’s latest offensive against Huawei pushes the global semiconductor industry into uncharted territory; it may also harm American interests in the process. And, flattening the other curve—could fossil fuels be added to covid-19’s casualty list? Kenneth Cukier hosts. Runtime: 23 min  Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify |Google | Stitcher | TuneIn For more on the pandemic, see The Economist’s coronavirus hub. For access to The Economist’s print, digital and audio editions subscribe: www.economist.com/radiooffer